					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Depends on the game (e.g. SMB3 just uses extra RAM), but if you want to keep the memory usage low just keep the number of changeable items low, that's really the crux of it.<br /><br />...and just in case: if you aren't storing the state as a single bits rather than a whole byte, do that too for 8:1 more space.</div>

